{"name": "LifeStraw Flex with Gravity Bag", "categories": ["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Water bottles and water treatment", "Water filters, treatment and tablets", "Water filters", "Inline and filter water bottles", "Flex with Gravity Bag"], "description": "Versatile water filtration for where ever your adventure takes you. The microfilter can be used as a personal straw, attached to your hydration bladder or disposable water bottle, or hung off the reservoir for a gravity filter at base camp. A combination a membrane filter and an activated carbon filter produces safe and tasty water.Membrane microfilter treats up to 2000L (varies with water quality).Activated carbon filter treats up to 100L.Removes up to 99.99999% of waterborne bacteria, and up to 99.999% of waterborne parasites and microplastics.3.7L reservoir has webbing handle for hanging.Quick connect hose and backwashing syringe included.LifeStraw\u2019s Follow the Liters program provides a child in a developing country safe with drinking water for an entire school year with every LifeStraw product sold.", "product_code": "6012-388", "tech_specs": {"Weight": ["196g"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking", "Travel", "Emergency preparedness"], "Filter type\n\nWater can be treated using various types of filters, chemicals or non-chemical purification methods, or a combination. Filters on their own will not remove viruses as they are too small.": ["Hollow fibre technology"], "Output": ["0.5L/min"], "Cartridge life\n\nThe life of the filter cartridge is based on the quantity of water you can treat before the cartridge is no longer effective. This does not apply to battery operated or chemical filter systems.": ["2000L"], "Filter size\n\nA 0.5 micron or smaller filters protozoa and some large bacteria; 0.2 micron or smaller filters smaller bacteria such as campylobacter.": ["0.2microns"], "Effective against protozoa\n\nProtozoa are larger than one micron and include cryptosporidium and giardia.": ["Yes"], "Effective against viruses\n\nMost viruses are in the 0.1 micron size range, but they can be as small as 0.002 microns.": ["No"], "Effective against particulate\n\nParticulate consists of very small bits and pieces such as dirt or bugs.": ["Yes"], "Effective against bacteria\n\nBacteria can cause illnesses such as diarrhea and dysentery and are about 1.0 micron in size, although some can be as small as 0.2 microns.": ["Yes"], "Made in": ["Korea, Republic of"]}, "img_urls": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9146823868446/6012388-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9146816790558/6012388-NOC02-ALT-BOTTLE.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193345515550/6012388-NOC02-ALT-E.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193345646622/6012388-NOC02-ALT-F.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358426142/6012388-NOC02-ALT-A.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358491678/6012388-NOC02-ALT-B.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358622750/6012388-NOC02-ALT-C.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358721054/6012388-NOC02-ALT-D.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9146823868446/6012388-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9146816790558/6012388-NOC02-ALT-BOTTLE.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193345515550/6012388-NOC02-ALT-E.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193345646622/6012388-NOC02-ALT-F.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358426142/6012388-NOC02-ALT-A.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358491678/6012388-NOC02-ALT-B.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193358622750/6012388-NOC02-ALT-C.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-